intro paragraph : Underwater dredging is a delicate procedure, that when executed properly allows for full functionality of facilities and Maritime Traffic lanes. Accurate positioning and plow orientation are vital aspects to the “Dredging” process. With over more than sixty years experience, Crofton Diving proves to excel in dredging and underwater operations. Divers and supervisor positions are staffed with highly experienced individuals, accredited under Association of Diving Contractors International(ADCI). Crofton Diving Constantly thrives in maintaining the highest integrity for safety and approval of the compliance and regulations set by the Occupational Safety and Health Administration(OSHA) and the United States Coast guard (USCG). Crofton Barges equipped with cable laying rigs are set up and monitored by a four man dive crew.

A doctor was on the premises according to a Facebook message written by Scheer and her trainer, Eric Haycraft (other reports dispute this), but an ambulance was not. Haycraft, said, "I've been a fighter, coach and trainer in this business for 20 years, and there is always an ambulance at every fight, professional or amateur." According to Chike Lindsay-Ajudua, Simmons's boyfriend, it took over an hour for her to be driven to a hospital even though IKF president Steve Fossum claims to have arranged for an ambulance from a nearby firehouse to be on call. The IKF's website has a section of their coverage of the event set aside for debunking these and other rumors, but it's difficult to ascertain who is telling the closest thing to the truth.

World Boxing Council welterweight champion Andre “The Beast” Berto tore his left bicep in either the first or second round of his triumph over “El Indio” Carlos Indio Saturday night at the BankAtlantic Center in Sunrise, Fla. Berto (27-0, 20 KOs), who knocked Quintana (27-2, 21 KOs) out in the eighth round, underwent an MRI after the bout, and his doctor diagnosed him with a tear in the muscle Tuesday. “But my tendons are still intact as they can see,” said Berto, 26, a two-time National Golden Gloves winner, who captured 22 state titles in Florida. “So I am gonna have to ice it and rest for a few weeks, so the swelling can go down and then start rehab.” Berto further emphasized that his injury is not overly severe. “But the doctor said it should be fine. Not a serious tear, just needs time to heal.”

Brian C.Saturday, October 29, 2011 at 3:12pm EDT

lift light, about a 3rd or half what you normally lift in high reps / time lapsed intervals. Due to the nature of movement you're body will be undergoing for fighting, it will need to run at critical states of exhaustion..." bigger tanks require more energy".....but if kept at a resistance where there constantly working, muscular endurance will increase along with high calorie fat burn giving you a shredded look.

Legalize LeeThursday, April 12, 2012 at 9:53am EDT

Just over a week away from The Hampton Roads Cannabis Festival at Town Point Park! This is WHY we are having the 4-20 event... Please invite and bring as many people as you can! A show of numbers and influence first. We have to show the elected officials how many of us are willing to take a stand for our rights, and make them understand that this is something that co-workers, neighbors, friends, parents, soccer moms, cancer patients, cancer survivors, college professors, preschool teachers, doctors, lawyers, accountants, politicians, city workers, students, athletes, and every other demographic on the planet use on a regular basis. This is the ONLY issue that crosses into every single demographic of people in the world. This is a personal, civil, state's, public health, constitutional, and an unalienable rights issue that MUST be addressed and corrected. The second fold to this event is marching to city hall and having speakers give personal accounts of WHY they have chosen to stand up publicly to END the prohibition of cannabis. We will also have a proclamation to sign urging elected officials to support our efforts in legalization.

Legalize LeeThursday, April 19, 2012 at 9:37am EDT

Well folks, we are a day away!! I just wanted to thank everyone that has helped us with this event, and send out some important info. First of all the after party will be at All-Out Tattoo located at 1540 Azalea Garden Rd. Norfolk, VA. 23502. This location is in a commercial district, so there are no noise ordinances we have to worry about, (can we say party till dawn!?!?!?) and there is plenty of room for everyone! Our supporters at Alll-Out are even going so far as keeping 3 artists on staff to hook up those sweet 4-20 tattoos for us at a discounted price! As far as town point park goes, we are gathering at 4pm. We will have a countdown for 4:20. No Dreads is opening the Festival, playing an acoustic set until 4:30 when we will have the hoola hoop contest. 710- OIL will then pick up and play from 445-515. We will then march to City Hall where we will have 2 speakers about the failed war on Cannabis. Please dress as festively as possible!
